__NAME__ purpose
specify default URL separator character
__END__


__NAME__ synopsis
<arg choice='plain'><replaceable>non_word_character</replaceable></arg>
__END__


__NAME__ description
Specify URL separator character for &IC;-generated &glos-HTML; links.
Only one character is allowed, and the only recommended ones are
the default <literal>&amp;</literal>, <literal>;</literal> or
<literal>:</literal>.
__END__

__NAME__ see also
MV_HTML4_COMPLIANT
__END__

__NAME__ example: Setting UrlSepChar
<programlisting>
UrlSepChar :
</programlisting>
__END__

